Reasoning: The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for storing and manipulating sets, multisets, and sequences of integers. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of succinct data structures, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper presents applications of the indexable dictionary data structure to encoding k-ary trees and computing prefix sums, which are topics in algorithms (cs.AL).
